idinfo.useconst: Under no circumstances may the data be redistributed or made available over a network without explicit permission from the Will County GIS Department. It is required that the Will County GIS Department be cited in any products generated from the data. The following source citation must be included: "Source: (Full Title)" For custom requests a client must submit a written request stating the intended applications for the data to the Will County GIS Department. When the request is granted, data may be used only for the purposes explicitly stated in the written request.

All warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to the implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, freedom from contamination by computer viruses or hackers and non-infringement of proprietary rights are disclaimed. Changes may be periodically made to the information herein; these changes may or may not be incorporated in any new version of the publication. If you have obtained information from any of the County web pages from a source other than the County pages, be aware that electronic data can be altered subsequent to original distribution. Data can also quickly become out of date. It is recommended that careful attention be paid to the contents of any data, and that the originator of the data or information be contacted with any questions regarding appropriate use. metainfo.metuc: This metadata file is intended to accompany the geospatial data set identified and received from Will County. It is not to be altered or summarized. Will County does not support secondary distribution. If this geospatial data set was received from anyone besides Will County, this metadata file and the geospatial data set it describes may lack integrity. Please send questions or comments to Contact in Metadata Reference.
